The '''Living Art Marine Center''' is a Marine Science Education Center in the city and county of [[Honolulu]] in the state of [[Hawaii]]. Developer of [[Hawaiian Sealife]], [[Richard Xie]], founded the Living Art Marine Center in 2010. The Living Art Marine Center focuses on educational programs and interactive activities about marine life and the importance of sustainability within the oceans around the world.<ref>{{cite web|title=Living Art Marine Center| publisher=Aloha Update| last=Lewis| first=Leoni|url=http://www.alohaupdate.com/2011/07/12/living-art-marine-center/|date=12 July 2011}}</ref>

Tours of the aquarium must be booked in advance, and are intended for children. At the end of the tour visitors can make [[gyotaku]] print shirts or shell necklaces. There is also an area where visitors can touch [[Sea cucumber|sea cucumbers]], [[Hermit crab|hermit crabs]], and other small marine animals.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://honolulufamily.com/blogs/living-art-marine-center-world-underwater-thrills-kids/|title=The Living Art Marine Center: A World of Underwater Thrills for Kids|last=Coligny|first=Ashley de|date=2012-08-16|work=HONOLULU Family|access-date=2018-04-14|language=en-us}}</ref>

